│ The user wants me to fix a crash in LLVM's `LoopAccessAnalysis`.                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ **1. Analyze the crash**                                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The crash is an assertion failure: `AddressSpace == AS && "all pointers in a checking group must be in the same address space"`. This happens in                                         │
│ `llvm::RuntimeCheckingPtrGroup::addPointer` within `llvm/lib/Analysis/LoopAccessAnalysis.cpp`.                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The reproducer shows a loop accessing the same underlying `alloca` through pointers with different address spaces (3 and 4). The `LoopAccessAnalysis` pass tries to group these accesses │
│ for runtime dependency checking. The assertion indicates that it's incorrectly trying to put pointers from different address spaces into the same `RuntimeCheckingPtrGroup`.             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The backtrace points to `RuntimePointerChecking::groupChecks` as the place where pointers are grouped. This function iterates over equivalence classes of pointers. The root cause is    │
│ likely that the equivalence relation used to group pointers does not properly account for the address space.                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ **2. Locate the source of the problem**                                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The equivalence classes are built in `AccessAnalysis::canCheckPtrAtRT`. This function uses `AliasAnalysis` to determine if two pointers might alias. If they do, they are put into the   │
│ same equivalence class.                                                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The core of the issue is that `AAResults::alias` can report `MayAlias` for two pointers that point to the same underlying object, even if they have different address spaces (due to     │
│ `addrspacecast`). The `LoopAccessAnalysis` logic then assumes they can be grouped for runtime checks, but the runtime check grouping logic (`RuntimeCheckingPtrGroup`) is designed to    │
│ work only with pointers in a single address space.                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ **3. Propose a solution**                                                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ A simple and direct fix is to prevent pointers with different address spaces from being considered equivalent in the first place, within the context of `LoopAccessAnalysis`.            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ In `AccessAnalysis::canCheckPtrAtRT`, before calling `EC.unionSets(I->getData(), J->getData())` based on the alias analysis result, we should add a check to ensure that the pointers'   │
│ address spaces are the same.                                                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The relevant code snippet is in `llvm/lib/Analysis/LoopAccessAnalysis.cpp`:                                                                                                              │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ // Collect all may-aliasing pointers.                                                                                                                                                    │
│ for (auto I = Pointers.begin(), E = Pointers.end(); I != E; ++I) {                                                                                                                       │
│   for (auto J = I; J != E; ++J) {                                                                                                                                                        │
│     if (I == J)                                                                                                                                                                          │
│       continue;                                                                                                                                                                          │
│     if (LAI.getAAResults()->alias(I->getData(), J->getData()))                                                                                                                           │
│       EC.unionSets(I->getData(), J->getData());                                                                                                                                          │
│   }                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ }                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ Here, `I->getData()` and `J->getData()` are `Value*` pointers. We can get their types and then their address spaces.                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fix is to add a condition:                                                                                                                                                           │
│ `if (I->getData()->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() == J->getData()->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace())`                                                                            │
│ before the `EC.unionSets` call.                                                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This change will ensure that pointers are only grouped if they have the same address space, which will prevent the assertion failure in `RuntimeCheckingPtrGroup`.                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ **4. Implement the fix**                                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will use `sed` to insert the address space check into `llvm/lib/Analysis/LoopAccessAnalysis.cpp`.                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The line to modify is:                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ `if (LAI.getAAResults()->alias(I->getData(), J->getData()))`                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will change it to:                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ `if (LAI.getAAResults()->alias(I->getData(), J->getData()) && I->getData()->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() == J->getData()->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace())`                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This ensures that even if `alias` returns true, we don't union pointers from different address spaces.                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i 's/if (LAI.getAAResults()->alias(I->getData(), J->getData()))/if (LAI.getAAResults()->alias(I->getData(), J->getData()) \&\& I->getData()->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() == │
│ J->getData()->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace())/' llvm/lib/Analysis/LoopAccessAnalysis.cpp                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
